The mesh is a knitted  composite-type mesh designed to be partially absorbable and lightweight. It is constructed primarily from polypropylene  with a layer composed of polyglecaprone to enhance absorbability. The mesh is available in square or rectangular shapes with size 10 cm x 15 cm. It has a weight of 88 grams per square meter (gsm)  with a pore size of 2.0 mm x 2.0 mm and a minimum polypropylene content of 30 gsm. The mesh has a thickness of 0.5 mm and demonstrates an initial burst strength of 313 N/cmÂ². After the absorption of the polyglecaprone 25 layer  the burst strength is reduced to 215 N/cmÂ². The mesh is sterilized using ethylene oxide

Anatomical mesh (3D Mesh) is made from non-absorbable monofilament polypropylene textile and has a large pore design. Flexible 3D construction allows a prompt fibroblastic response through the interstices of the mesh. Its unique 3D design conforms to the inguinal anatomy. There is a blue monofilament orientation marker (M) and arrow. Polypropylene anatomical (3D) mesh has a pore size of 1.0 mm x 1.5 mm  a weight of 1.56g and a thickness of 0.55 mm. It has a uniaxial tensile strength of 65 N  a biaxial tensile strength of 100 N  and a burst strength of 93.16 N/cmÂ². The mesh is sterilized using ethylene oxide.
